test_exception_lower
====================

Pins down the contract that the `saw-tools/exception-lower` pass is
expected to produce: throws become flag-set + sentinel return, catches
become flag-check + clear, and unhandled paths re-raise by re-setting
the flag.

The test only depends on `$SAW` and the committed `error-return-value.bc`,
so it runs in CI without the exception-lower binary (or LLVM dev headers)
being available.  The pass's own end-to-end behaviour - actually
rewriting `invoke`/`landingpad`/`catchpad`/etc. - is exercised by the
developer harness under
[`saw-tools/exception-lower/test/`](../../saw-tools/exception-lower/test/).

Regenerating the bitcode
------------------------

    make regen

requires a working `clang++`.  The current artefact was built with the
version recorded in `error-return-value.bc.FROM`.
